history.content: If you email cs-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu with this question & include your student ID, I will take a look @ this & communicate with you privately. I did check on CS168 & there is a waitlist that you should have been able to add yourself to.

After being dropped from the Cryptography 194 (not enough people signed up), I was told that there was still time to repurpose my Phase 1 credits.

Does anyone have any other suggestions for technical courses that would be still open at this point in time (as in, NOT waitlist position #200+)?

All the upper divs I am looking at still say "open" (with the green dot and everything), except I don't qualify for reserved seating (despite being in the EECS major, senior standing, all lower divs completed, etc.)

(I believe we need at least 8 units, and without Crypto I'm down to 4.)
